article.headline: Cleveland St. 83, Green Bay 75
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Norris Cole matched his career high with 21 points and Cedric Jackson flirted with a triple-double to lead Cleveland State past Wisconsin-Green Bay 83-75 on Saturday night. J'Nathan Bullock added 18 points and Chris Moore had 13 for the Vikings (19-8, 10-5 Horizon League). Jackson had 11 points, 10 rebounds and eight assists in 31 minutes. The Vikings rolled to a 16-0 lead and were on top 34-24 before the Phoenix (19-8, 11-4) made a late run to cut the lead to 71-70 on a Ryan Tillema basket with under 3 minutes left. George Tandy followed that with a bucket and after Green Bay cut the lead to 75-73 on a Rahmon Fletcher layup with a minute left, Moore countered with a basket with 39 seconds left to push the lead back to four. The Phoenix never got closer again. Tillema had 18 points, Mike Schachtner 15, Troy Cotton 13, Randy Berry 12 and Fletcher 10 for Green Bay.
